  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002K.agda" type="external">erct-002K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>, with <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections and retractions</link> given by <link href="erct-002I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002I" title="Composition of sections">composites of the component sections</link> and <link href="erct-002J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002J" title="Composition of retractions">retractions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10584</anchor> <rss>erct-002L.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002L</addr><route>erct-002L.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> maps</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002L.agda" type="external">erct-002L.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex> is quasi-invertible, with sectionhood and retractionhood witnesses given by those of the <link href="erct-002I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002I" title="Composition of sections">composites of the component sections</link> and <link href="erct-002J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002J" title="Composition of retractions">retractions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10585</anchor> <rss>erct-003J.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-003J</addr><route>erct-003J.xml</route>  <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>11</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link> maps</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003J.agda" type="external">erct-003J.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A \to  C</tex> is <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10586</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>   <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>11</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002C" href="erct-002C.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, it suffices to find a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> to the composite <tex>g \circ  f</tex>; we take this to be the composite (<ref addr="erct-002L" href="erct-002L.xml" taxon="Construction"/>) of the underlying <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverses</link> of <tex>f</tex> and <tex>g</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10587</anchor> <rss>erct-000Y.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000Y</addr><route>erct-000Y.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Section-retraction pair</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000Y.agda" type="external">erct-000Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>s  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> and <tex>r  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a pair of maps. A homotopy <tex>h  \colon  r \circ  s  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibits <tex>s</tex> as a <em><strong>section</strong></em> of <tex>r</tex> and <tex>r</tex> as a <em><strong>retraction</strong></em> of <tex>s</tex>. Together, <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( s,r \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> are referred to as a <em><strong>section-retraction pair</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10588</anchor> <rss>erct-002K.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002K</addr><route>erct-002K.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002K.agda" type="external">erct-002K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>, with <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections and retractions</link> given by <link href="erct-002I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002I" title="Composition of sections">composites of the component sections</link> and <link href="erct-002J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002J" title="Composition of retractions">retractions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10589</anchor> <rss>erct-002L.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002L</addr><route>erct-002L.xml</route>  <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> maps</title>   <meta name="source">
  
  
