</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex> is quasi-invertible, with sectionhood and retractionhood witnesses given by those of the <link href="erct-002I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002I" title="Composition of sections">composites of the component sections</link> and <link href="erct-002J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002J" title="Composition of retractions">retractions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>